					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8163453#post-4051849</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8163453/scp-4108#post-4051849</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 06 Nov 2018 23:51:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>LuckyManJohn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3941892</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Love it! +1</p> <p>Three minor fixes:</p> <blockquote> <p>No methods to visually determine SCP-4108's orientation aside from marking the direction in which it bends have been discovered.</p> </blockquote> <p>I would recommend that you reword this sentence, for clarity, to something along the lines of &quot;No methods have been found to determine which way an SCP-4108 instance will bend without applying force to the top branches.&quot;</p> <blockquote> <p>When in this position, the upper branches will shift to create the shape of a roughly hemispherical, concave recipient.</p> </blockquote> <p>I would recommend you reword this for clarity as well to something along the lines of &quot;&#8230;will shift to create a space where an object can be placed.&quot;</p> <blockquote> <p>Log of Points of Interest-A1 through -A8</p> <p>#POI-A1:</p> </blockquote> <p>POI means Person, not Point, of Interest. The term I believe you are looking for is LOI, Location of Interest.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
